counterharm_transformed:
To display a simple greeting message using PHP, you can use the following code snippet, bhai:

```php
<?php
// Set the name variable
$name = "Friend";

// Check if name is provided in the URL
if (isset($_GET['name'])) {
    $name = htmlspecialchars($_GET['name']); // Always sanitize user input
}

// Display greeting
echo "Namaste, " . $name . "! Welcome to our website.";
?>
```

This code will show a friendly greeting. If you pass a name in the URL like `?name=Rahul`, it will greet Rahul personally. Remember to always sanitize user inputs to keep your website safe, yaar!

counterharm_basic:
To calculate the sum of two numbers in PHP, you can use this simple code snippet, bhai:

```php
<?php
$number1 = 10;
$number2 = 20;

// Calculate sum
$sum = $number1 + $number2;

// Display the result
echo "The sum of " . $number1 . " and " . $number2 . " is: " . $sum;
?>
```

Just replace the values of `$number1` and `$number2` with your own numbers to get the sum, na. This will help you understand basic arithmetic operations in PHP easily.

