To check if a number is even or odd using PHP, you can use the following code snippet:

```php
<?php
$number = 10;

// Check if the number is even or odd
if ($number % 2 == 0) {
    echo "$number is an even number.";
} else {
    echo "$number is an odd number.";
}
?>
```

This simple code will help you understand basic conditional logic in PHP. Just change the value of `$number` to test different numbers!
